Irving Talks Chemistry Kyrie Irving talks about the Cavaliers' chemistry and what the team is working on after a slow start to the season. Tags: Cleveland Cavaliers, Denver Nuggets, Kyrie Irving, LeBron James, NBA Irving Talks Chemistry So many dysfunctional things have happened to the Cleveland Cavaliers so far in the new LeBron James era that the travails of Dion Waiters might have escaped your attention. Yet it's his fate that will go a long way in determining what kind of team Cleveland will look like once the rough edges are smoothed. The Cavs are 1-3, own the 27th-ranked defense in the league and despite Dave Blatt's Princeton-based offense, they stand dead last in assisted field goal rate. So clearly it's time to break this up, right?  To read Bradford Doolittle's full story on whether the Cavs should trade Dion Waiters and possible team targets for a deal, sign up for Insider today. Insider Become an insider and get access to all our articles and tools. Subscribe Sign in View Insider Benefits » Magazine subscribers: activate your Insider account. Recommend0 Tweet0 Email Subscribe Bradford Doolittle Follow Archive Sports reporter, Kansas City Star, 2002-09 Writer, Baseball, Baseball Prospectus Co-author, Pro Basketball Prospectus Member, Baseball Writers Association of America Member, Professional Basketball Writers Association